{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In hindsight, Aria {\i really} shouldn\u8217't have pushed that button.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The young woman had been weeding one of the fields on her tiny farmland when, suddenly, she felt her rake run across something metallic half-buried in the soil. It took her a bit of digging around to discover that what she had initially thought was a small piece of litter, was in fact a human-sized pod buried beneath the earth.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria considered simply leaving the pod there and calling someone to pick it up. However, she also happened to spy a large red button on the side. And Aria, as sensible as she liked to believe she was, was a sucker for a large red button. So she pressed it.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"STAND BACK, UNKNOWN LIFEFORM, OR FACE INCINERATION!\u8221" The pod suddenly blared. Steam hissed from the pod-door as it began to open. \u8220"REVIVING SUBJECT FROM STASIS!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria could only watch in terror as a humanoid lifeform in a bulky spacesuit slowly stepped out.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Do not be afraid.\u8221" It said in a calm, male voice. \u8220"I have come to help.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 That was when Aria hit it with the rake.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Ow!\u8221" The thing wailed as it fell to the ground, facescreen cracked. \u8220"The hell was that for, lady? I said I came in peace!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"You expect me to believe that?\u8221" Aria said, clutching her weapon. \u8220"Your pod threatened to incinerate me!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"What?\u8221" The man (?) turned towards the pod from which he had emerged. \u8220"Why would you say that, FT028? This is supposed to be a peaceful mission! You\u8217're not even armed!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"I THOUGHT IT MIGHT ADD DRAMATIC FLAIR.\u8221" The pod blared again. \u8220"ALSO I PANICKED.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Oh. Well, in that case, I apologise for my AI.\u8221" The man said. \u8220"I suppose your reaction was understandable considering the dystopia you live in.\u8221" Before Aria could ask him what he meant by that, he gave a sharp, military salute. \u8220"Let\u8217's start introductions again. My name is Major Michael Harper of Project Restoration. And you are?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Aria.\u8221" Aria gave him a suspicious look. \u8220"You alien?\u8221" She paused. \u8220"Not that there\u8217's anything wrong with that.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Eheh. I\u8217'm afraid not.\u8221" Harper said. \u8220"Although I can understand why you might think that way. No, in fact, I am a human, like you, but from the {\i diiiiistant paaaast!!}\u8221" He said while twiddling his fingers in what he seemed to think was a dramatic way.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"\u8230?Is that so?\u8221" Aria said.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Harper paused. He put down his hands. \u8220"You seem unimpressed.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"What? Oh, no I\u8217'm very impressed.\u8221" Aria lied. \u8220"So what are you doing here from the {\i diiiistant paaaast?}\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Well, I\u8217'm-\u8220" Harper paused mid-sentence. \u8220"Are you making fun of me?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"A little.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Hmph. Well, I guess I can\u8217't hold that against you.\u8221" Harper sighed. \u8220"You\u8217've probably had a very hard life, what with the rape gangs, plague and oppression.\u8221" Before Aria could emphatically deny this, Harper threw up his hands dramatically. \u8220"But fear not! All will change now that I\u8217'm here! I have come from the past, to save the future!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria blinked. \u8220"Save it from what?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Simple.\u8221" Harper said. \u8220"FT028, please prepare the story of Project Restoration.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"AFFIRMATIVE.\u8221" The pod beeped. \u8220"BUMBADUMBUMBUMBUMBUMBADUMBUMBUM-\u8220"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Um\u8230?\u8221" Aria slowly backed away from the pod. \u8220"What\u8217's it doing?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Merely laying down an appropriately dramatic background score for my explanation.\u8221" Harper said. \u8220"There wasn\u8217't room in the databanks for a recorded song, so FT028 provides its own.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"If it doesn\u8217't stop now, I\u8217'm going to hit it with the rake.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"\u8230?FT028, maybe tone the music down a little.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"AW. BUT I NEVER GET TO LAY DOWN MY FUNKY-FRESH BEATS.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria blinked. \u8220"Funky-fresh? You really are from the distant past...\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Anyway\u8230?\u8221" Harper continued. \u8220"Project Restoration was started in the 2200\u8217's. Humanity was at its peak technologically and socially. However, we felt a duty to later generations who would feel civilization's inevitable collapse into dystopia. As such, several of the best men and women of the age were placed in stasis pods and hidden away to survive into the future. Upon awakening, they would then rebuilt humanity from the ashes with their superior technological and sociological skills! And thus\u8230?\u8221" Harper threw his hands up dramatically as FT028 began to \u8216'play\u8217' dramatic music. \u8220"I am here to save you all!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria took all this in silently. Then she spoke.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Um... I don't think the future really needs saving. We\u8217're basically fine.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Fine?\u8221" Harper chuckled. \u8220"How na\u239?ve. Maybe from your point of view, you\u8217're fine, but I can tell otherwise just from this farmland. According to our records, 500 years ago, this land was a city. Obviously the entire place was flattened in some sort of nuclear blast/alien war/demon invasion and nature has only just started to recover.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Oh no, actually, all of this is just cultivated.\u8221" Aria corrected. \u8220"Part of our attempts to foster Earth\u8217's ecosystem after we moved all our cities onto orbiting satellite spaceships.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Harper blinked. \u8220"Really? Um\u8230? Are you sure there wasn\u8217't a nuclear war?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Yeah.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Not even a little one?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Nope.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Maybe a nuclear skirmish?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"I think I\u8217'd have heard about it.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Well, what about your leaders?\u8221" Harper asked. \u8220"I bet, by now, you\u8217're entering the 100th year of the reign of your genocidal cyborg dictator, HitlerStalinTron 3000 or something, right?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Nope.\u8221" Aria said. \u8220"Still largely democratic voting. Sure there are still problems here and there, but when aren\u8217't there with any democratic process?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Er\u8230?\u8221" Harper seemed rather taken back by this news. \u8220"W-Well, what about the air? I bet centuries of pollution has left it near inhospitable! I bet if I took off my helmet I\u8217'd be choking in a matter of minutes.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Well, you\u8217'll find out fairly soon.\u8221" Aria said. \u8220"Your helmet\u8217's leaking.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Harper paused. \u8220"What?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Your helmet.\u8221" Aria motioned to a crack in his facescreen, from which the low whistle of escaping air could be heard. \u8220"Leaking.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Oh God!\u8221" Harper immediately flew into a panic, pressing his hand against the crack in a futile attempt to stem the air. \u8220"Atmosphere plating cracked\u8230? clean air escaping\u8230? toxic radiation\u8230? flooding\u8230? in\u8230?\u8221" He slowly collapsed to the ground, making loud, wheezing sounds.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Aria watched him thrash about for a few moments. \u8220"You seem fine.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Harper stopped mid-flail. Then, cautiously, he sucked in a quick breath. \u8220"Huh. Guess I am. So the air\u8217's breathable too, then?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Well, yeah. What were you expecting it to be like?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Let\u8217's not go into that.\u8221" Harper said, getting back to his feet. \u8220"You\u8217're sure there are no toxins in the air? Nuclear fallout? Toxic waste? Even a little?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Nope.\u8221" Aria shook her head. \u8220"All clean and breathable.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Really? How come I can smell bitter almonds?\u8221" Harper said, a little too smugly for someone seemingly hoping to choke to death. \u8220"That\u8217's a telltale sign of cyanide.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Or a telltale sign that I baked an almond shortcake 20 minutes ago.\u8221" Aria said, fishing a slice out of her satchel. \u8220"Want some?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"\u8230?I\u8217'll pass.\u8221" At this point, Harper was beginning to look genuinely frustrated that he wasn\u8217't dying. \u8220"So is there anything wrong with the world right now? Any reason for me to be revived? Any reason at all for me to have spent several generations asleep in that cramped, uncomfortable pod?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"I get the feeling you\u8217're a little bitter.\u8221" Aria said.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"A little.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"I DO DETECT THAT BITTERNESS LEVELS ARE SLIGHLY RAISED AT THIS POINT IN TIME.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Not helping, FT028.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Well\u8230? I suppose there may be something wrong\u8230?\u8221" Aria racked her brains for anything to sate this increasingly frustrated \u8216'distopia expert\u8217'. \u8220"Um\u8230? Sometimes, the cybernet connection is a bit spotty. And, er, the garbage chute sometimes overflows. It only gets collected once a fortnight, so-\u8220"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Wait.\u8221" Harper froze. \u8220"You don\u8217't have day-to-day garbage disposal?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"No\u8230?\u8221" Aria said slowly and cautiously.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"My God, woman!\u8221" Harper said violently shaking her. \u8220"What dystopian hellscape are you living in where garbage is not promptly disposed of?! This is worse than I expected!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Um\u8230?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"But fear not!\u8221" Harper said, posing dramatically. \u8220"For I have come from the distant past to aid you in restoring humanity to its former glory! You shall have your garbage disposed of in a timely and convenient fashion! This is what Project Restoration was built for!\u8221" He patted the flank of his pod. \u8220"Come FT028. Let us make plans to fix this new world!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"MAY I SUGGEST WE START BY INCINERATING IT?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"We\u8217'll file that as Plan B!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"YAAAAAAAAY!\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u8220"Okay then.\u8221" Aria said, slowly backing away. \u8220"You two\u8230? do that. In the meantime, I\u8217'm going to quickly make a call\u8230?\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
